---
title: DataCite - Assign DOIs
---

<header class="image-bg-fixed-height-small">
  <div class="jumbotron">
    <h1>
      Assign DOIs
    </h1>
  </div>
</header>

<section>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-9 section-content">
        <h1>service description</h1>
        <p>
          A Digital Object Identifier (DOI) is an alphanumeric string assigned
          to uniquely identify an object. It is tied to a metadata description
          of the object as well as to a digital location, such as a URL, where
          all the details about the object are accessible.
        </p>
        <%= image_tag "services_doi_1.png", :width => '300' %>
        <p>
          In order to create new DOIs and assign them to your content, it is
          necessary to become a <%= link_to 'DataCite member', 'become.html' %>
          or work with one of the
          <%= link_to 'current members', 'members.html' %>.
        </p>
        <p>
          Through the web interface or the API of the
          <%= link_to 'DataCite Metadata Store', 'https://mds.datacite.org' %>
          you will be able to
          submit a name, a metadata description following the
          <%= link_to 'DataCite Metadata Schema',
          'http://schema.datacite.org' %>
          and at least one URL of the object to create a DOI. Once created,
          information about a DOI is available through our different services
          <%= link_to 'search', 'search.html' %>,
          <%= link_to 'event data', 'eventdata.html' %>,
          <%= link_to 'OAI-PMH', 'oaipmh.html' %>
          and others).
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-3 bg-primary sidebox">
        <h1>access details</h1>
        <ul>
          <li> Accessible through:
            <br /> <i class="fa fa-external-link"></i>
            <%= link_to 'https://mds.datacite.org',
            'https://mds.datacite.org' %>
          <li>
            Intended users:
            <ul>
              <li>- DataCite members
                <br />- Users
            </ul>
          <li> Availability:
            <br /> <i class="fa fa-external-link"></i>
            <%= link_to 'http://status.datacite.org',
            'http://status.datacite.org' %>
        </ul>
        <h1>learn more</h1>
        <ul>
          <li>Technical documentation:
            <br /> <i class="fa fa-external-link"></i>
            <%= link_to 'https://mds.datacite.org/static...',
            'https://mds.datacite.org/static/apidoc' %>
          <li>DOI Handbook:
            <br /> <i class="fa fa-external-link"></i>
            <%= link_to 'https://doi.org/10.1000/182',
            'https://doi.org/10.1000/182' %>
          <li>Wikipedia entry:
            <br /> <i class="fa fa-external-link"></i>
            <%= link_to 'Digital object identifier',
            'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digital_object_identifier' %>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
